HEADWORD: Nitid
<hw>Nit"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>nitidus</ets>,
fr. <ets>nitere</ets>. See 3d <er>Neat</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Bright; lustrous; shining.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Gay; spruce; fine; -- said of persons.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>T. Reeve.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nitranilic</ent>⟦br⟧
